Design and d√©veloppementLe S. 13 is the first seaplane designed by the Societa Idrovolanti Alta Italia (RAIS) for civil passenger transport. It was a seaplane, a biplane with room for five passengers. The S. 16 was powered by a single engine Fiat A. 12bis. The military versions were equipped with a bow cockpit equipped to accommodate an observer-gunner and spears, and bombs mounted under the wings. The military version was sold to Brazil, Soviet Union, Spain, and Turkey.
Military Version of the S. 16bis with cockpit front, the USSR exploited this version (80 aircraft) - named S-16bis, some examples were built under license in Spain.
